The paper deals with visual counting, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new approach to address the open-set problem in counting objects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method that involves deep learning, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with datasets and performance evaluation, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
